# Build context for the Keywordista Docker image. The Dockerfile only
# ever needs source — never build artifacts, never the existing macOS app
# bundle, never Xcode noise. Excluding these keeps `docker build` cold-
# start small (faster on every dev box, faster on CI) and prevents stale
# bytes from a previous `swift build` accidentally ending up inside the
# image.

# Swift / SPM artifacts (but NOT Package.resolved — when CI runs
# `swift package resolve` before the docker build, the resulting
# lockfile pins exact dependency versions for a reproducible image.
# Locally it's gitignored; the Dockerfile's `COPY Package.resolved*`
# glob handles either presence cleanly.)
.build/
.swiftpm/

# Node artifacts — Docker rebuilds the SPA in its own builder stage.
web/node_modules/
web/dist/

# Built SPA — Docker rebuilds it from web/ via the spa-builder stage.
# (Including this would risk shipping a stale Public/ from a local
# `npm run build` instead of the one matching the source we're shipping.)
Public/

# macOS app build outputs
mac/.build/
mac/Keywordista.app/
releases/

# Git, IDE, OS noise
.git/
.github/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
*.xcuserstate

# Docs / examples / human-only files — never reach the runtime image.
README.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
LICENSE
docs/
*.md
*.html

# NOTE: Tests/ is NOT excluded here. Package.swift declares
# `.testTarget(name: "AppTests", path: "Tests/AppTests")`, so SPM
# expects the directory to exist when it loads the manifest in the
# swift-builder stage. The test target is never *built* in the runtime
# image (the runtime stage only COPYs the App binary + Public assets),
# so this is a few KB of build-context cost and zero runtime-image cost.

# Local env / secrets — must NEVER end up in build context.
.env
.env.*
*.p8
*.key

# Misc
*.log
.remember/
.superpowers/
.claude/
